                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9416.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-27T18:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 27, 1913—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>587. My October 25, 9 p.m. I believe the document in my possession is authentic.
                    It is at any rate an expression of Huerta’s electoral ideas and may be taken as
                    a basis for action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
